cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS

The paper deals with image segmentation, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). It also involves the use of deep neural networks (cs.LG) and optimization algorithms (cs.DS). The paper proposes a new algorithm for image partitioning that does not require explicit seeds or a tunable threshold, which could fall under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper mentions the use of an objective function that is related to integer linear programming, which could fall under the category of neural networks and learning (cs.NE).
